# Design System Rules — Figma MCP Integration

Rules for integrating Figma designs into this codebase using the Model Context Protocol.

---

## 1. Token Definitions

**Current state:** No formal design tokens. Values are hardcoded in CSS.

**Colors (extract to tokens when scaling):**
```css
/* src/index.css, src/App.css */
--bg: #1a1a1a;
--text-primary: #ffffff;
--text-secondary: #f0f0f0;
--text-muted: #a4a4a4;
```

**Typography:**
- **DM Mono** (monospace): titles, section labels — `font-family: 'DM Mono', ui-monospace, ...`
- **DM Sans** (sans): body, links, subtitles — `font-family: 'DM Sans', system-ui, ...`
- Title: 24px, body: 16px

**Spacing (8pt grid):**
- Gaps: 2px, 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px
- Page padding: 200px vertical, 24px horizontal
- Section gaps: 16px, 24px, 32px

**Recommendation:** Add `src/styles/tokens.css` with CSS custom properties when introducing more screens.

---

## 2. Component Library

**Location:** Components live in `src/App.tsx` (no separate component folder yet).

**Patterns:**
- Functional components with TypeScript
- Props typed via `type` or `interface`
- Reusable pieces: `TypingText`, `Section`

```tsx
// Example: Section component pattern
type SectionProps = {
  label: string
  items: { title: string; href: string }[]
  expandable?: boolean
}

function Section({ label, items, expandable = true }: SectionProps) { ... }
```

**No Storybook.** Consider adding when component count grows.

---

## 3. Frameworks & Libraries

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| UI | React 19 |
| Language | TypeScript 5.9 |
| Build | Vite 7 |
| Styling | Plain CSS (Tailwind installed but not configured) |
| Fonts | Google Fonts (DM Sans, DM Mono) |

**Vite config:** `vite.config.ts` — minimal, React plugin only.

---

## 4. Asset Management

**Storage:**
- `public/` — static assets served at root (e.g. `/cedric-photo.png`)
- `src/assets/` — imported assets (e.g. `react.svg`)

**Usage:**
```tsx
// Public assets — absolute path
<img src="/cedric-photo.png" alt="" />

// Imported assets
import logo from './assets/react.svg'
<img src={logo} alt="React" />
```

**No CDN.** No explicit optimization (Vite handles bundling).

---

## 5. Icon System

**Current:** No icon library. Inline SVGs or img tags only.

**Recommendation:** Add an icon component when needed; consider `lucide-react` or similar if adopting shadcn.

---

## 6. Styling Approach

**Methodology:** Plain CSS with BEM-like class names.

**Structure:**
- `src/index.css` — global reset, body, base styles
- `src/App.css` — component-specific styles (imported in `App.tsx`)

**Class naming:**
```
.page, .page-inner
.profile-layout, .profile-panel, .profile-header
.profile-title, .profile-subtitle, .profile-links
.section, .section-label, .section-list, .section-more
```

**Responsive:**
```css
@media (max-width: 960px) {
  .profile-panel { margin-left: 0; max-width: none; }
}
```

**No CSS Modules, no styled-components.** Single global stylesheet per concern.

---

## 7. Project Structure

```
cclee.design/
├── index.html          # Entry HTML, font preconnect, Google Fonts
├── src/
│   ├── main.tsx         # React mount, imports index.css
│   ├── index.css        # Global styles
│   ├── App.tsx          # Main app + inline components
│   ├── App.css          # App-specific styles
│   └── assets/          # Imported assets
├── public/              # Static assets (served at /)
├── vite.config.ts
├── tsconfig.json
└── package.json
```

**Figma node tracking:** Root frames use `data-name` and `data-node-id` for MCP alignment:
```tsx
<main className="profile-layout" data-name="main" data-node-id="51:2">
```

---

## Figma MCP Integration Checklist

1. **get_design_context** — Use `nodeId` and `fileKey` from Figma URL to fetch code.
2. **get_screenshot** — Call after `get_design_context` for visual reference.
3. **Token mapping** — Map Figma variables to existing colors/typography above.
4. **Layout** — Use `max-width: 1200px`, `margin: 0 auto` for page-inner; 8pt grid for gaps.
5. **Fonts** — Ensure DM Sans / DM Mono are loaded in `index.html` before use.
6. **Assets** — Place in `public/` and reference with `/filename.ext`.
